Subject: [PATCH] libsysbase: static config.h; drop broken self-rebuild rules

Two small fixes to the libsysbase subdir we added in patch 0003:

1. Makefile.in shipped from the Cygnus-era template had
      Makefile: Makefile.in config.status @host_makefile_frag_path@
      config.status: configure
   rules that expect libsysbase/configure to exist.  Our build pipeline
   uses the parent libgloss configure to AC_CONFIG_FILES libsysbase/
   Makefile directly (patch 0002); there IS no libsysbase/configure,
   so those rules cause `No rule to make target 'configure'` during
   make-recursion.  Drop them.

2. libsysbase/*.c do `#include "config.h"` expecting an autoconf-
   generated header defining HAVE_ELF / HAVE_GNU_LD / REENTRANT_
   SYSCALLS_PROVIDED / etc.  On a modern GNU PowerPC-ELF toolchain
   all of those are definitionally true, so ship a static config.h
   rather than carry libsysbase's broken Cygnus-era configure.in
   infrastructure just to have autoconf fill in the blanks.

With these two in place plus patches 0002 (parent wiring) and 0006
(newlib <_ansi.h> compat), libgloss/libsysbase builds cleanly and
produces libsysbase.a in $PS3DEV/ppu/powerpc64-ps3-elf/lib/.

diff --git a/libgloss/libsysbase/Makefile.in b/libgloss/libsysbase/Makefile.in
--- a/libgloss/libsysbase/Makefile.in
+++ b/libgloss/libsysbase/Makefile.in
@@ -141,8 +141,6 @@ info:
 install-info:
 clean-info:

-Makefile: Makefile.in config.status @host_makefile_frag_path@
-	$(SHELL) config.status
-
-config.status: configure
-	$(SHELL) config.status --recheck
+# Parent libgloss configure generates this Makefile via AC_CONFIG_FILES;
+# no subdir-local configure exists, so drop the self-rebuild rules that
+# the Cygnus-era template carried.
diff --git a/libgloss/libsysbase/config.h b/libgloss/libsysbase/config.h
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/libgloss/libsysbase/config.h
@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@
+/*
+ * libsysbase static config.h for the PS3 LV2 target.
+ *
+ * Replaces the autoconf-generated header we would otherwise get from
+ * libsysbase's Cygnus-era configure.in.  On a modern GNU PowerPC-ELF
+ * toolchain every HAVE_* below is definitionally true, so we just
+ * hard-code them rather than carry the broken autoconf infrastructure.
+ *
+ * REENTRANT_SYSCALLS_PROVIDED is on because PSL1GHT's librt installs
+ * _r-suffixed syscall hooks into __syscalls at startup (crt1.c).
+ */
+#ifndef _PS3_LIBSYSBASE_CONFIG_H_
+#define _PS3_LIBSYSBASE_CONFIG_H_
+
+#define HAVE_ELF                      1
+#define HAVE_GNU_LD                   1
+#define HAVE_ASM_PREVIOUS_DIRECTIVE   1
+#define HAVE_ASM_POPSECTION_DIRECTIVE 1
+#define HAVE_SECTION_ATTRIBUTES       1
+#define REENTRANT_SYSCALLS_PROVIDED   1
+
+/* No __SYMBOL_PREFIX on PowerPC ELF. */
+#define __SYMBOL_PREFIX ""
+
+#endif /* _PS3_LIBSYSBASE_CONFIG_H_ */
